    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte Trinitatis. Anno Domini millesimo centesimo octavo,
                        regnante <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/127">Heinrico</persName>
                        rege anno secundo, die tercio mensis iunii, indictione prima, in <placeName
                            ref="#places/3520">Cornucervina</placeName>. Petivi a te domno <persName
                            key="#Prevosts #Priors"><name ref="Gregorius Pomposianus"
                                >Gregorio</name></persName>, <rs key="#Prevosts">preposito</rs>
                        <rs key="#Priors">priori</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Confinia #Rivers #Casalia #Penalty #Rent_in_money #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Marie de <placeName
                                ref="#places/4179">Pomposia</placeName></orgName>, tibi et pro
                        persona <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/4305">Alberti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs> predicti <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterii</rs>, uti me presente <persName><name
                                ref="Iohannes de Petro">Iohanne de Petro</name></persName> de
                            <placeName ref="#places/4617">Albaro Longo</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis">libelli</rs> afficti nomine
                        concedisti mihi meisque filiis et heredibus rem iuris predicti monasterii,
                            <rs key="#Casalia">casale</rs> unum scilicet positum in <placeName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Casalia" ref="#places/4601">
                            Miliarini</placeName>, quod habet in longitudine sua … et in <rs
                            key="#Size">latum pedes sedecim</rs>; ab uno latere iura <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/3659">Sancte
                            Marie de Aurigario</orgName>, alio latere et ab inferiori capite
                        possident heredes <persName key="#Confinia">
                            <name ref="Martinus de Anna">Martini de Anna</name></persName> et a
                        superiori capite <rs key="#Roads">via</rs> et <rs key="#Rivers">fluvius</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Confinia #Rivers" ref="#places/4196">Padus</placeName>
                        percurrit. Concedisti ad habendum, tenendum, possidendum, supersedendum per
                        me vel per meos missos defensandum, meliorandum in annis advenientibus
                        viginti et novem ad renovandum, dantibus pro renovatura solidos decem
                        Veneticorum Et ut in omni nativitate Domini pensionem dare debeam me meosque
                        filios et heredes ad predictam dominacionem <rs key="#Rent_in_money"
                            >denarios quatuor Veneticorum et amisirem unum</rs>. Promittens preterea
                        promitto ego antedictus petitor et pro meis filiis et heredibus hanc
                        peticionis paginam inviolabiliter modis omnibus adimplere et conservare
                        vobis vestrisque successoribus, sub pena <rs key="#Penalty">unius uncie
                            auri</rs>, et soluta pena in sua maneat firmitate. Quam scribere rogavi
                            <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Dominicus">
                            Dominicum</name></persName> Dei nutu <rs key="#Notary">notarium</rs> sub
                        die, mense et indictione prefata. + Signum manus predicti Iohannis de Petro
                        petitori ad omnia predicta. + + + + Signa et nomina testium hec sunt:
                        Vitalis de Blanca, Dominicus de presbitero Gaudioso, Bonus de Teucia et
                        Tuido eius filius testes rogati ad omnia predicta.</ab>
                </div>
